# Changelog

All notable changes to the Solana Ontology SDK will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [0.1.0] - 2025-01-01

### Added
- Core ontology types, loader, and JSON Schema validator (`@solana-ontology/core`)
- Anchor IDL v0/v1 parser with codemod and concept generator (`@solana-ontology/idl-parser`)
- Runtime SDK with transaction lifecycle, signers, PDA derivation, and queries (`@solana-ontology/sdk`)
- TypeScript and Rust code generators from ontology concepts
- Client library generator for React applications (`@solana-ontology/generator-client`)
- Ontology Metadata Service (OMS) REST API server (`@solana-ontology/oms`)
- MCP server for LLM agent interaction (`@solana-ontology/mcp-server`)
- IDL ingestion pipeline (`@solana-ontology/ingestion`)
- CLI tool (`@solana-ontology/cli`)
- 38 seed ontology concepts across 6 categories (primitive, token, defi, governance, infrastructure, delivery)
- Docker support with multi-stage builds and docker-compose
- Cross-package integration test

### On-Chain Linkage Fields (added in 0.1.0+)
- `pdaSeeds` — formal PDA seed structure for type-safe derivation
- `accountLayout` — Borsh account layout with discriminator and field offsets
- `programId` — default on-chain program ID (base58)
- `idlInstruction` — link to IDL instruction for code generation
- `tokenStandard` — SPL vs Token-2022 variant

### Token-2022 Support
- TokenExtension concept with Token-2022 program ID mapping
- TransferFeeConfig, MetadataPointer, PermanentDelegate, ConfidentialTransferMint extension concepts
- `tokenStandard: "spl" | "token2022"` field on token concepts

### Kinetic Layer
- `TransactionLifecycle` with build → simulate → sign → dispatch → confirm pipeline
- Auto-adjust compute unit limit from simulation result (20% margin)
- `KeypairSigner`, `KmsSigner`, `MpcSigner` signer implementations
- `ActionBuilder` for composing typed instructions
- `derivePdaFromConcept` for concept-driven PDA derivation

### MCP Server
- JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdio and HTTP transports
- OAuth bearer token authentication for HTTP transport
- Resources and tools auto-generated from ontology concepts

### OMS
- Pluggable storage backends: `MemoryStorage` and `SqliteStorage`
- REST API for Object Types, Link Types, and Action Types
- External adapter plugin system

### CI
- GitHub Actions workflow for build, test, and lint on push/PR
